    a fabio:JournalArticle .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.3897/zookeys.1171.104142.figure1>
    dc:description "Figure 1. Phylogeny of Novochares spp. Part 1: Novochares punctatostriatus, Novochares tectiformis, Novochares sallaei, Novochares orchis, Novochares minor, and Novochares garfo species groups. Inferred from COI and 28 S combined sequence data. Numbers next to taxon names are extraction numbers (see Table 1). The Novochares portion of the phylogeny of Acidocerinae based on five gene fragments as presented in Short et al. (2021) is reproduced in the lower left corner for comparative purposes." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/881168" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.3897/zookeys.1171.104142.figure26>
    dc:description "Figure 26. Aedeagi of the Novochares tectiformis species group A-C N. yora D-F N. mojenos G-K N. coya L N. atlanticus A, D, G, I, K, L dorsal view B, E ventral view C, F, H, J lateral view G, H Trinidad I, J Peru K Guyana." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/881193" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.3897/zookeys.1171.104142.figure29>
    dc:description "Figure 29. Distribution of Novochares tectiformis species group A N. duo (red), N. bolivianus (yellow), N. atlanticus (blue), N. danta (green) B N. coya (red), N. yora (yellow), N. xingu (blue), N. mura (green), N. trifurcatus (purple) C N. tectiformis (red) D N. pume (red), N. piaroa (yellow), N. florifer (blue), N. mojenos (green), N. tambopatense (purple)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/881196" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

